[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 25/100 start id=gsm8k_test_326
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 25/100 path 1/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 25/100 path 1/3 answer='14'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 25/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 25/100 path 2/3 answer="Let's denote the number of people who got on the bus at the terminal as \\( x \\). According to the information given:\n\n1. At the first bus stop:\n   - Initial number of people = \\( x \\)\n   - People got in = 5\n   - Total after the first stop = \\( x + 5 \\)\n\n2. At the second bus stop:\n   - People got out = 7\n   - People got in = 8\n   - Total before reaching the third stop = \\( (x + 5) - 7 + 8 \\)\n\nWe know that after these stops, there were 20 people heading to the third stop.\n\n3. Therefore, we can set up the equation based on the given conditions:\n   \\[ (x + 5 - 7 + 8) = 20 \\]\n\n4. Simplify the equation:\n   \\[ x + 6 = 20 \\]\n   \\[ x = 20 - 6 \\]\n   \\[ x = 14 \\]\n\nSo, the number of people who got on the bus at the terminal was 14."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 25/100 path 3/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 25/100 path 3/3 answer='14'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 25/100 done id=gsm8k_test_326 prediction='14' gold='14' correct=True vote_counts={'14': 2, "Let's denote the number of people who got on the bus at the terminal as \\( x \\). According to the information given:\n\n1. At the first bus stop:\n   - Initial number of people = \\( x \\)\n   - People got in = 5\n   - Total after the first stop = \\( x + 5 \\)\n\n2. At the second bus stop:\n   - People got out = 7\n   - People got in = 8\n   - Total before reaching the third stop = \\( (x + 5) - 7 + 8 \\)\n\nWe know that after these stops, there were 20 people heading to the third stop.\n\n3. Therefore, we can set up the equation based on the given conditions:\n   \\[ (x + 5 - 7 + 8) = 20 \\]\n\n4. Simplify the equation:\n   \\[ x + 6 = 20 \\]\n   \\[ x = 20 - 6 \\]\n   \\[ x = 14 \\]\n\nSo, the number of people who got on the bus at the terminal was 14.": 1}
