[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 45/100 path 3/3 answer="Step 1: Calculate Elvis's savings goal for the entire month.\nElvis aims to save $1125 per month.\n\nStep 2: Determine how many days are in the second half of April.\nApril typically has 30 days, so the second half consists of 15 days (since there are two halves).\n\nStep 3: Set up an equation to find out how much Elvis needs to save each day in the second half.\nLet \\( x \\) represent the amount saved each day in the second half.\n\nStep 4: Create an equation based on the given condition and solve for \\( x \\).\nThe total savings in the second half would be \\( 15x \\), which should equal double the savings in the first half. The first half includes all but one day of the second half, so it amounts to \\( 14x + x = 15x - x = 14x \\). Thus:\n\\[ 2(14x) = 15x \\]\n\nStep 5: Solve the equation.\nDivide both sides by \\( x \\):\n\\[ 28 = 15 \\]\nThis simplifies to:\n\\[ x = \\frac{15}{7} \\approx 2.14 \\]\n\nTherefore, Elvis has to save approximately $2.14 each day in the second half of the month."
