[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 87/100 path 3/3 answer="Step 1: Calculate how much land was sold initially.\nAbraham sold half of the land for $50.\n\nStep 2: Determine the total cost of the first sale.\nSince half of the land (which is 40 square meters) was sold for $50, we can find the price per square meter by dividing $50 by 40 square meters.\n\nStep 3: Calculate the amount of land sold in the second transaction.\nAfter the first sale, half of the remaining land was sold for $30.\n\nStep 4: Find the number of square meters sold in the second transaction.\nThe remaining land after the first sale is 40 - (half of 40), which equals 20 square meters. Since this amount was sold for $30, we divide $30 by 20 square meters to find the price per square meter.\n\nStep 5: Combine all the costs to determine the total earnings from all sales.\n\nLet's do the math:\n\n- Cost per square meter from the first sale:\n\\[ \\frac{50}{40} = \\$1.25 \\]\n\n- Amount sold in the second transaction:\n\\[ \\frac{30}{20} = \\$1.50 \\]\n\n- Total earnings:\n\\[ 50 + 30 + (20 \\times 1.25) = 50 + 30 + 25 = \\$105 \\]\n\nTherefore, Abraham will be able to earn a total of $105 after selling all his unused land."
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 87/100 done id=gsm8k_test_1161 prediction='140' gold='170' correct=False vote_counts={'140': 1, '170': 1, "Step 1: Calculate how much land was sold initially.\nAbraham sold half of the land for $50.\n\nStep 2: Determine the total cost of the first sale.\nSince half of the land (which is 40 square meters) was sold for $50, we can find the price per square meter by dividing $50 by 40 square meters.\n\nStep 3: Calculate the amount of land sold in the second transaction.\nAfter the first sale, half of the remaining land was sold for $30.\n\nStep 4: Find the number of square meters sold in the second transaction.\nThe remaining land after the first sale is 40 - (half of 40), which equals 20 square meters. Since this amount was sold for $30, we divide $30 by 20 square meters to find the price per square meter.\n\nStep 5: Combine all the costs to determine the total earnings from all sales.\n\nLet's do the math:\n\n- Cost per square meter from the first sale:\n\\[ \\frac{50}{40} = \\$1.25 \\]\n\n- Amount sold in the second transaction:\n\\[ \\frac{30}{20} = \\$1.50 \\]\n\n- Total earnings:\n\\[ 50 + 30 + (20 \\times 1.25) = 50 + 30 + 25 = \\$105 \\]\n\nTherefore, Abraham will be able to earn a total of $105 after selling all his unused land.": 1}
