[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][gsm8k] sample 90/100 path 2/3 answer='First, calculate the amount of water removed by each speed over their respective times.\n\n- Low setting: \n  - Water removed = 1 liter/day * 3 days = 3 liters\n\n- Medium setting:\n  - Water removed = 2 * (low setting) = 2 * 3 liters = 6 liters\n\n- High setting:\n  - Water removed = 2 * (medium setting) = 2 * 6 liters = 12 liters\n\nNext, sum the amounts of water removed:\n\n- Total water removed = low + medium + high\n- Total water removed = 3 liters + 6 liters + 12 liters = 21 liters\n\nTherefore, the total amount of water that the dehumidifier removed from the air in Brian’s basement is **21 liters**.'
