[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][csqa] sample 13/100 path 1/3 answer='The question asks about a runway specifically designed for extremely large cargo planes that can only land there.\n\n1. Consider the size of cargo planes and their capabilities.\n2. Think about airports where such aircraft would have access to runways with specific features or limitations.\n3. Identify options that match the characteristics needed for landing large cargo planes.\n4. Evaluate each option based on its relevance to accommodating very large cargo planes.\n\nFinal Answer: E. fashion show'
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][csqa] sample 13/100 path 2/3 start
[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][csqa] sample 13/100 path 2/3 answer='The question implies that an extremely large cargo plane has specific requirements for landing, which narrows down our options significantly.\n\n1. Consider the size and weight constraints of an extremely large cargo plane. This excludes small or medium-sized aircraft from being able to land on such runways due to their limited capacity and safety standards required for extreme loads.\n2. Eliminate backyard and bowling alley as they are too small and unstructured environments.\n3. A city can host multiple airports but typically does not have one dedicated exclusively for extremely large cargo planes.\n4. Military bases are designed with extensive infrastructure to accommodate various types of aircraft including very large ones like cargo planes.\n5. A fashion show involves temporary structures and venues without permanent facilities suitable for long-term operations involving extremely heavy equipment.\n\nThe final answer is E. military base.'
