[self_consistency][qwen2_5_1_5b_instruct][csqa] sample 95/100 path 2/3 answer='The correct answer is E. skin irritation.\n\nExplanation:\n\n1. Sexual activity often involves direct contact between partners.\n2. This contact increases the likelihood of bodily fluids being exchanged.\n3. Many sexually transmitted infections (STIs) and certain viral diseases can be spread through sexual intercourse.\n4. Among these, STIs like genital herpes or HIV have been linked to causing skin irritations due to sores or rashes on the affected areas.\n5. Therefore, engaging in unprotected sex carries the risk of transferring pathogens that could lead to skin irritation upon physical contact.'
